{"id": "duc04-testb-26:4#12", "contents": "South Africa's government is considering a new amnesty for those involved in apartheid-era violence, sparking debate over whether such a move would promote healing and reconciliation or undermine the country's pursuit of justice and accountability. While the proposal has received widespread support from various political parties, one political party is opposed to any form of new amnesty - the tiny but influential Democratic Party, a liberal group that was not involved in the violence."}
